commentary: Mutombodzi to Noor Ali Zadran, OUT this will peg them back a little! Noor Ali set himself for a slog sweep, but the ball was fuller and straighter than he was looking for and he completely lost his shape as he swung wildly to leg. The ball ballooned high off the top edge, and Chisoro sprinted to his left from mid on to set himself under the ball as it came down not far from the non-striker's end. It wasn't the easiest catch, but he clung on with both hands.

commentary: Mutombodzi to Nawroz Mangal, OUT what a catch! Long off is out, and Chisoro is up in the circle at mid on. Mangal top edged a swipe that was aimed over Chisoro's head, but the ball swirled in the direction of mid off. The long off fielder would never have been able to get there in time, but Chisoro charged across the field and tumbled forward as the ball rocketed towards the ground, getting a hand cleanly underneath it.

commentary: Chisoro to Mohammad Nabi, 1 run there's the hundred, his first in ODIs! Nabi glances the ball very fine on the leg side, and they charge back for the second. His team mates are all on their feet cheering him on from the changing room, and he lifts his helmet and bat in the air to acknowledge them, finally kneeling at the edge of the pitch to give thanks by performing the sajda. It's been a near flawless knock, and it's set his team up for a big total.

commentary: Masakadza to Mohammad Nabi, SIX runs this is the biggest six I've ever seen hit at Queens Sports Club. This is a day he'll remember.

commentary: Amir Hamza to Mutombodzi, OUT oh what a catch! Mutombodzi stepped back and lifted a drive inside out over extra cover, but couldn't get it quite square enough of the fielder running in from long off. It was Shafiqullah down there, I think, who is on as a sub fielder for Noor Ali. He had a lot of ground to cover, and had to dive too, but the ball stuck in his palm. Afghanistan snaffle another one!

Shenwari has set off for the midwicket boundary, roaring in celebration, and Shahzad looks like he wants to smash the disturbed stumps down! Raza is slumped in the crease. He didn't read this one, that zipped straight on without spinning and also kept really low. Afghanistan are well on top now!

text: a yorker bounces off Jongwe's left foot and rolls to leg, and they charge through for a leg bye.

commentary: Aftab Alam to Chigumbura, OUT Chigumbura departs! He'd not been able to find the boundary even once in this innings, and needed to hit out at every ball. This was the ball to hit - a length delivery on middle and leg - but he picked out the fielder at deep midwicket. An off, off-colour innings. Though Jongwe remains, this should be the game in the bag for Afghanistan.

commentary: Aftab Alam to Jongwe, FOUR runs Jongwe, meanwhile, is unfazed! Another length delivery is flapped up and over square leg, right into the gap, and away for four.
shortText: Aftab Alam to Jongwe, FOUR runs
text: Jongwe, meanwhile, is unfazed! Another length delivery is flapped up and over square leg, right into the gap, and away for four.

commentary: Aftab Alam to Jongwe, 1 run Aftab fires down a bouncer, and Jongwe hooks it down to fine leg to keep the strike.
shortText: Aftab Alam to Jongwe, 1 run
text: Aftab fires down a bouncer, and Jongwe hooks it down to fine leg to keep the strike.

commentary: Dawlat Zadran to Jongwe, 1 run a low full toss, on off stump, is slapped to mid-off.
shortText: Dawlat Zadran to Jongwe, 1 run

commentary: Dawlat Zadran to Masakadza, no run full and wide outside off, and Masakadza can't get close with a booming drive.
shortText: Dawlat Zadran to Masakadza, no run

commentary: Dawlat Zadran to Masakadza, no run definite, late reverse swing for Dawlat, away from the left-hander. Again it's full and wide outside off, and again he can't lay bat to ball.
shortText: Dawlat Zadran to Masakadza, no run

commentary: Dawlat Zadran to Masakadza, no run squeezed out to point, right off the toe end as it left him late through the air
shortText: Dawlat Zadran to Masakadza, no run

commentary: Dawlat Zadran to Masakadza, 1 run a full toss on middle is punted down the ground, but just the one run. Afghanistan won't mind that, as it means Masakadza may well be on strike again in the next over.
shortText: Dawlat Zadran to Masakadza, 1 run

commentary: Dawlat Zadran to Jongwe, OUT fierce yorker! Jongwe wanted to drive through extra cover, but this fast, reverse swinging yorker zipped under his bat in a flash. Dawlat Zadran celebrates, and Afghanistan close in on a series-leveling win.

commentary: Aftab Alam to Masakadza, OUT and another! Zimbabwe are crumbling away. Aftab followed Dawlat's cue and fired down a fast yorker right at the batsman's toes. Masakadza swung right over the top of it, and his middle stump was knocked clear out of the ground.

commentary: Aftab Alam to Nyumbu, 1 run tip-and-run single for Nyumbu, just behind point to get off the mark. Ironic cheers from the crowd.
shortText: Aftab Alam to Nyumbu, 1 run
text: tip-and-run single for Nyumbu, just behind point to get off the mark. Ironic cheers from the crowd.

commentary: Aftab Alam to Panyangara, 1 run Panyangara backs away and hacks a length delivery through the covers without much timing.
shortText: Aftab Alam to Panyangara, 1 run
text: Panyangara backs away and hacks a length delivery through the covers without much timing.

commentary: Aftab Alam to Nyumbu, OUT all done! Nyumbu slaps to point, but he doesn't want to run. Panyangara, however, does and keeps going even as his partner tries to send him back. Eventually Nyumbu decides he must go, but by then Aftab has the ball in his hands and he makes a mess of the stumps at the non-striker's end, rocketing a full strength throw at them from about half a foot away. An emphatic way to level the series!
